President Obama highlighted the importance of clean energy and the urgent need for comprehensive legislation during his visit to Trinity Structural Towers, a green manufacturing facility in Iowa. He emphasized that the development of clean, renewable sources of energy is crucial for the 21st-century global economy. The President's energy policy aims to create millions of clean energy jobs and jump-start the American Clean Energy sector. He also unveiled a program to develop renewable energy projects on the waters of the Outer Continental Shelf. The President emphasized the need for comprehensive legislation to protect the nation from economic and strategic risks associated with foreign oil reliance and climate change. The policies to advance energy and climate security include creating new jobs in the clean energy economy, promoting U.S. competitiveness, investing in energy research and development, breaking dependence on oil, producing more energy at home, promoting energy efficiency, closing the carbon pollution loophole, and protecting American consumers.